description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Now is the time to take the next step in your pharmacy career! This is a fantastic opportunity to join an award winning and expanding clinical pharmacy team and be part of our exciting future at East and North Hertfordshire NHS Trust! &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are looking for a high calibre and motivated pharmacist to join our team of Band 6 rotational clinical pharmacists here at the Lister Hospital in Stevenage (main site for East and North Hertfordshire NHS Trust). &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;You will be part of an innovative and progressive pharmacy team that puts patient care at the centre of everything we do. You will develop and expand your clinical knowledge through a structured rotational program that will include specialities such as general medicine, cardiology, care of the elderly, oncology / haematology, acute medicine, frailty, stroke, paediatrics, obstetrics / maternity, general surgery, colorectal surgery, trauma / orthopaedics, urology, plastics / ENT, elective surgery, dispensary, aseptics and medicines information. There will also be the opportunity to work within our renowned renal services unit (a tertiary referral centre providing expert renal and dialysis services for the East of England).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Our team is committed to both personal and professional development. We will fund and support post graduate training including Postgraduate Diploma in Clinical Pharmacy Practice followed by non-medical prescribing (where relevant). &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Relevant hospital pharmacy experience is desirable but not essential. We also encourage applications from community based pharmacists. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This really is a great time to join East and North Hertfordshire NHS Trust…… If this sounds like the opportunity for you, please get in touch with us!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; Interviews to be held week commencing 30th November 2020&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For more information please contact:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mark Leamon (Pharmacist Manager for Clinical Services) &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
